column11: Comments

A production and warehouse property in the Konala industrial area changed hands in a transaction completed at the end of December. The asset is multi-let to six tenants and sits on an owned plot of approximately 8,200 sqm.

column4: Storebrand Nordic Real Estate Fund II
column11: Storebrand made its first direct real estate investments in Finland through the acquisition of two residential properties in Espoo via off-market transactions. The assets comprise 376 apartments and align with the fund’s core-plus strategy focusing on housing in strong Nordic locations.

Balder Finland acquired a fully let big box retail property in Kuopio’s established retail and light industrial area. The property is leased to machinery rental company Renta, providing stable single-tenant income.

Balder Finland acquired a modern logistics center in Seinäjoki leased to Huhtala Logistics, Kesko and Halpahalli. The property is energy-efficient, utilizing geothermal heating and waste heat recovery, and supports food and goods distribution.

Cibus acquired a grocery-anchored retail project in Vantaa developed by Hartela, with Tokmanni as the main tenant. The property is a forward-funded project with construction starting in early 2026 and forms part of Cibus’ broader multi-country acquisition program.

Cofinimmo acquired two care facilities under development from Toivo as part of a broader letter of intent covering multiple projects in Finland. The properties are pre-let on long-term leases to Esperi Care and are scheduled for delivery in 2026 and 2027, strengthening Cofinimmo’s Finnish healthcare portfolio.

Citycon sold 275 residential apartments connected to the Lippulaiva shopping center at IFRS book value to reduce leverage. The divestment supports Citycon’s strategy to focus on Nordic shopping centers and recycle capital into core assets.

Alma Property Partners and Cobbleyard acquired the historic Apollo House with plans for a major renovation while retaining office use. The project targets high-quality, flexible office space in Helsinki’s prime CBD, respecting the building’s heritage values.

Kinland acquired a daycare project from Toivo Group, marking the first transaction between the two parties. The property is fully developed by Toivo, pre-let on a long-term lease to Norlandia Daycare Centers, and scheduled for completion in August 2026.

Mandatum and Morgan Stanley established a joint venture targeting residential assets in the Helsinki metropolitan area, seeded with seven properties. The platform reflects renewed international institutional interest in Finnish residential real estate.

Julius Tallberg acquired a portfolio of three big-box retail properties in Tampere as part of its strategy to expand outside the Helsinki region. The assets are fully leased to strong national retail tenants in a well-established retail cluster.

Public Property Invest completed the acquisition of SBB’s entire Finnish social infrastructure portfolio, comprising 144 properties. The transaction significantly scales PPI’s platform and positions it as Europe’s largest listed social infrastructure owner.

The Finnish Seamen’s Pension Fund divested its entire residential portfolio into a new joint venture with Premico, transitioning to an indirect investment model. The portfolio includes 463 apartments across three cities and will be actively managed to enhance long-term value.

Sicore Real Assets acquired DHL Express’s newly developed main logistics and sorting center in Finland. The transaction highlights continued demand for prime, ESG-compliant logistics assets despite a more challenging investment market.

Kinland acquired a portfolio of 13 daycare properties as part of its accelerated expansion in the Finnish social infrastructure market. The deal follows two earlier acquisitions this month and further strengthens Kinland’s exposure to long-leased assets backed by strong demographic fundamentals.

Stendörren acquired a fully let production and warehouse property in Järvenpää under a long-term lease to a single tenant. The transaction marks Stendörren’s fourth Finnish acquisition this year and supports its strategy of building scale in the Helsinki metropolitan region.

column5: Lapti / Graniittiasunnot Oy / Oy Wedeco Ab
column11: Northern Horizon completed three separate acquisitions of care properties across Finland, adding 132 care places to its newest fund. The transactions expand the fund’s Finnish portfolio to 47 properties and underline continued investor appetite for modern, long-leased care assets.

Kesko acquired the Iso-Valkeinen property complex in a sale-and-leaseback arrangement while investigating long-term redevelopment for a future K-Rauta store. The acquisition secures a strategically located site with zoning optionality for retail development in the 2030s.

Hämeenmaa acquired the Heinola City Hall and Council House properties with plans to develop a new S-market in the city centre. The buildings will remain in municipal use until 2027, after which redevelopment is subject to zoning changes.
MVH strengthens position in special needs housing (164 apartments); Rinnekodit continues as operator
WAULT ~11 yrs; portfolio of 7 energy-efficient modern assets
Sixth asset in the joint portfolio; total portfolio value >€33M
Mega-scale DC project (up to 400 MW). Construction begins 2026; includes an energy park.
41-bed care facility, geothermal + solar, energy class A, BREEAM, completion 2027.
Fully leased portfolio; energy certificates A/B; strengthens Kinland’s Finland portfolio to ~200 assets.
Ethos’ largest deal to date; multi-city portfolio of light industrial facilities.
Fully leased, built 2024. State-of-the-art technical level.
LOI for turnkey development project. Construction starts 2026, completion 2027.
Rare prime-location Helsinki rental portfolio acquisition.
Includes Heikanrinne care center, Forssa fire station, Forssa main health center + Lehtimaja assisted living. Requires approval of borrowing authority.
Preliminary agreement signed. Building completed in 1982; used by The Association of Local and Regional Authorities and related bodies. HGR begins development planning immediately.
196-room Original Sokos Hotel Kupittaa sold to Balder. Located in major development area; Tuloskiinteistöt advised.
Third acquisition in Finland. Built 2021. Long-term lease; tenant covers major OpEx elements. Price also stated as SEK 134m.

column5: VP Facilities; Famdell Oy Ab; Kvadraten Ab
column11: Balder acquires 100% of KOy T2 Partners Vaasa Fab. Buildings from 1980s–2000s, originally for Wärtsilä. Extensive upgrades in 2022 for Primo Finland. Strengthens Balder Finland’s production/industrial portfolio. EY advised seller; Waselius Attorneys advised buyer.

Kesko sells 10 grocery properties to Prisma in a long-term sale & leaseback. Portfolio includes new & recent assets. Supports Kesko’s strategy of reinvesting in strategic stores and renovating nationwide network. Strengthens Prisma’s grocery-anchored portfolio and surpasses its Finland volume target.
Cooperative purchases land with 6,000 m² permitted BTA for future grocery store. Dalbo is a key growth area and strengthens Varuboden’s Åland service network.
Keskimaa signs conditional deal to buy municipal commercial property for future grocery development. Existing library and clinic services relocating before takeover.

Stendörren acquires modern 2021 logistics asset 13 km from Helsinki CBD. Fully let on 11-year lease with strong NOI and low operating risk, supporting long-term value creation. Estimated yield of 6.7%.

Prisma acquires four fully leased retail properties totalling ~15,000 m² from Innovestor. Assets include solar panels and battery systems improving energy efficiency and providing stable long-term income.
Prisma buys a 5,000 m² retail development in Raseborg from Tekova. Completion expected autumn 2026; fully pre-let to two discount retailers on 10-year leases and construction begins in 2025.
Keva acquires a landmark mixed-use portfolio including Old Student House, Kaivotalo, Citytalo and Grand Hansa. Mrec IM & HGR will manage and develop the culturally significant assets.

column4: Bonava Suomi & Suomen Asunnot ja Tontit I Ky
column11: Taaleri’s land fund sells a full development plot in Lauttasaari for €6.5m to Bonava and Suomen Asunnot ja Tontit. The property has increased in value since its 2016 acquisition and supports the fund’s controlled exit strategy.

Hanza acquires Lehto Group’s 10,000 m² factory property in Oulainen for €4.7m. Most of the purchase price is used to repay Lehto’s restructuring-linked bank debt; the asset expands Hanza’s adjacent manufacturing operations.
Nordiqus acquires three newly built school and daycare properties totaling 3,600 m². Assets have WAULT 19.5 years and high sustainability features including log construction and A-energy ratings.

A CapMan-managed fund sells the 35,000 m² Finnish National Board of Antiquities’ Collection and Conservation Centre in Vantaa to another CapMan fund. The asset, now fully leased to Senate Properties, was converted from logistics to public use with A-class energy efficiency and EU taxonomy compliance.

column5: Alma Property Partners & Mrec Investment Management
column11: Kesko acquires a majority stake in the Tikkurila shopping center in Vantaa from Alma Property Partners and Mrec Investment Management. The existing mall will be demolished, and Kesko plans to develop a new K-Citymarket on the site towards the end of the decade as part of a broader city center redevelopment with SRV.

column4: Evernord Real Estate Fund VI & Mirlux Oy
column11: Evernord Group (Lithuania) entered Finland with Mannerheimintie 168B acquisition in Helsinki. Acquired majority with Mirlux Oy (minority). To be redeveloped into mixed-use complex with 56 apartments, retail & offices. Evernord manages €350M AUM across Baltics & Spain.
Former development project; CapMan exited after 1.5 years due to strong returns. Fully leased to city under long-term lease to 2042. 4 buildings, 38,000 m² plot.
GEM advised on the sale of Pulttitie 9–11 in Roihupelto, Helsinki, owned by The Deaconess Institute. Fully leased.
Nyfosa’s Kielo acquired an 8,300 m² big-box retail property under development in Kuopio from Tekova. Fully leased, annual rent €1.5M, WAULT 8.1 yrs. Completion Sept 2026.

Brookfield and MESH Group formed a joint platform and acquired a six-property residential portfolio from ABRDN, including Unity Living assets in Helsinki (Jätkäsaari) and Tampere (Pyynikki). Operated as studio hotels with furnished apartments, coworking, and gyms. This marks Brookfield’s expansion into Nordic residential alongside its existing Nordiqus venture.

column4: Isojoki Data Center Oy (to be established)
column11: Isojoki Municipality to sell 180 hectares of land to Isojoki Data Center Oy for €10M, forming a major data center cluster project. Includes an additional €0.5M donation to education. Project to be zoned and construction-ready by Sept 2026. Aims to establish sustainable, energy-efficient infrastructure and boost local employment.

column4: Turku Technology Properties Oy (jointly owned by Hemsö & City of Turku)
column11: Turku Technology Properties acquired Arken campus (13 buildings, 15,000 m²) in Turku Science Park from Åbo Akademi Foundation for €43M. Fully leased to Åbo Akademi University for 20 years. Historic complex renovated 2001–2004.

Onvest Oy acquired a 3,000 m² office building in Järvenpää from Varte Oy, housing Varte’s equipment center. Simultaneously, the parties agreed to co-develop two business premises projects in the Helsinki Metropolitan Area, with construction starting H1 2026.

Prisma Properties acquired a newly built 2,600 m² Jula store in Konala, Helsinki from Hartela for €5.5M at a 7% yield. Ten-year lease with Jula, chain’s first store in the Helsinki area. Strengthens Prisma’s Finnish portfolio to three cash-generating assets.

Cobbleyard Real Estate acquired Bolero Business Park’s C-building in Pitäjänmäki, Helsinki from a BNP Paribas–managed fund. The building (completed 2006) has 5,500 m² of leasable space and forms part of the three-building Bolero Business Park (built 2004–2007).

Prisma Properties acquired two income-generating retail properties from Investor Partners for EUR 8.7 million. The assets total approximately 5,500 m² and are located in Pietarsaari (tenant: Rusta) and Seinäjoki (tenants: Puuilo and Barot’s). Annual rent ~EUR 1.25 million. Transactions closed on 1 Oct 2025 and mark Prisma’s first cash-flowing Finnish acquisitions.

Prisma Properties entered into a forward purchase agreement with Tekova for a new 5,000 m² shopping center in Iisalmi valued at EUR 6.2 million. The project, fully pre-let to discount retailers, will begin construction in late 2025 and complete in Q2 2026. The property will be developed to modern energy standards and strong retail micro-location. Advisors: Hannes Snellman, Erottaja Attorneys, Granlund, Naava Partners, Navigator Partners.

Public Property Invest (PPI) acquired three care property projects from Hartela for EUR 28 million. Total area ~8,000 m² across Kirkkonummi, Kaarina, and Lieto. Tenants: Attendo (Kirkkonummi) and Kototiimi Oy (Kaarina & Lieto) on 15-year leases with ~EUR 1.85 million annual rent. Construction begins in 2025; completion expected between late 2026 and spring 2027. Projects meet EU taxonomy and energy class A standards.

Hemsö acquires Hollola social welfare center (5,200 m², built 2021) from the municipality for €13.6m (~156 mSEK). Tenants include Päijät-Hämeen Welfare Association and Fimlab Oy. Deal approved by municipal council; closing early 2026.

Tekova signs agreements to sell two self-developed commercial projects to two investors for a combined ~€19.4m (~223 mSEK). Construction starts 2025; completion expected 2026. Transfers finalize upon project completion.

Cityvarasto acquires two properties: (1) ~1,000 m² retail/association property in central Riihimäki, tenanted by K-market and artists, to be converted into self storage by 2026; (2) ~1,300 m² building in Kerava Jäspilä business area, to open as storage facility Sep 2025.

column4: Selena Kiinteistöt Ky (JV: Keva & Axiom Advisors Oy)
column6: Helsinki metro, Tampere, Turku, Vaasa, Kuopio (18 properties)
column11: Keva and Axiom Advisors form Selena Kiinteistöt Ky, transferring 18 commercial properties (~182,000 m²) from Keva into the new company. JV aims to boost occupancy, returns, and competitiveness; Axiom takes over management and development.

Terrieri Kiinteistöt launches its second-largest investment ever: a 14,500 m² logistics project for Lehtipiste in Tuusula. Construction began June 2025, completion expected autumn 2026. Lehtipiste will centralize logistics operations from Vantaa, Jyväskylä, and Järvenpää.
City of Helsinki sells land in Herttoniemi to Fira and MTu-Consulting for €20m. Development will include a 10,500 m² arena and ~24,000 m² housing.
Sale and lease-back of a production and warehouse property in Myllynummi, Kerava, built in 1992
Portfolio of three retail properties in Vaasa, Jyväskylä and Oulu. The properties are built between 2005-2015. The largest tenants are Tokmanni, Puuilo, Musti ja Mirri, and Liikku
Slättö's Evolv has acquires 7 properties through 4 separate transactions. The properties are located in Helsinki, Espoo and Vantaa
Commercial property in Otaniemi, Espoo, sold to KY (Aalto University Business Student Foundation). HGR Property Partners acquired the property in April 2025
Biltema acquires land at Åland to develop a new Biltema, which will be c. 7,200 sqm upon completion in 2027

Capman has acquired a residential property in Katajanokka, Helsinki, completed in 2017. The asset will be managed under Capman’s newly established Leona concept, with planned energy investments aimed at achieving BREEAM In-Use Excellent certification and EPC A rating

Kalasatama Health and Wellbeing Centre in Helsinki sold for c. EUR 100M. The property was built in 2017, is fully let and located next to the shooping center Redi. City of Helsinki is the largest tenant. Deka Immobilien is selling, through its institutional property fund WestInvest ImmoValue

Lähitapiola is divesting Riihimäki Travel Centre, located in the centre of Riihimäki. The complex has c. 4,100 sqm of retail premises, and 4,100 sqm of office premises. The office premises are acquired by Riihimäki Tilat ja Kehitys Oy (RTOY), while Häme University of Applied Sciences (HAMK) has purchased the other part, which will be rebuilt into a new campus for HAMK

Care facility currently under construction in Haaga, Helsinki. The property is leased to a leading care provider on a 15-year lease agreement. At completion (Aug 2026), the gross rental income is estimated to EUR 1.3M

A modern light industrial property located close to Helsinki Airport, in the Koivuhaka industrial area. The property was completed in 2013 and comprises 4,400 sqm of high specification light industrial and auxiliary office premises. The tenant base is diverse

The Finnish special investment fund eQ Yhteiskuntakiinteistöt (eQ Community Properties) has acquired a combined school and business park property located in Niittykumpu, Espoo, from Varma Mutual Pension Insurance Company for €43.9m.  In connection with the deal, Varma also became an investor in the eQ Yhteiskuntakiinteistöt fund. The size of Varma’s fund investment has not been disclosed by the parties. The property's main tenant is the City of Espoo. The other part of the property is known as Uusikumpu Business Park and is an office building, c. 3,000 sqm is currently vacant

SRV and Balder have signed an agreement concerning the sale and completion of the Torihotelli project in central Oulu (144 room Scandic Go Hotel). Construction will resume in autumn 2025, and the hotel is expected to open in summer 2026. Torihotelli was originally expected to be completed in 2019. After the bankruptcy of the original developer, Kiinteistö Oy Oulun Torihotelli, SRV—acting as both the contractor and main creditor of the bankruptcy estate—continued to manage and develop the site during the construction break

Cibus acquires in Finland through two separate transactions. Five properties are a sale and lease-back with Tokmanni, who signs 10-year lease agreements in connection with the transaction (15,700 sqm). The properties in the first transaction are in Eurajoki, Kuopio, Pälkäne, Sipoo and Sodankylä. The other transaction concerns a property leased to S-Group in Tuusula (9,300 sqm)

Onvest has sold a property in Lappeenranta. The property is fully leased to Onninen Oy and is situated in Lappeenranta's Leiri commercial area, next to Prisma. It is a well-defined property for technical trade, featuring spaceous yard areas
Stendörren acquire fully let warehouse property for SEK 70M. 10-year lease agreement with an estimated NOI of SEK 5.5M (7.9%)

Balder's subsidiary Sato acquires 1,000 rental apartments in HMA, Turku, Tampere, Oulu and Jyväskylä. The units are spread over 16 residential properties, most of which are multi-family, but also some townhouses

Hemsö acquires Salpausselkä secondary school in Lahti, which accomodates 650 students and was built in 1958. In connection with the acquisition, a new 20-year lease agreement has been signed with the City of Lahti. The seller is a privately owned local company

Logistics asset in Piispankylä in Vantaa, in close proximity to the airport. The property comprises c. 7,000 sqm of high-quality logistics space. The asset is leased to two established logistics operators. Urban Light is a JV between Alea Partners and Alma

Prisma makes its first acquisition in Finland, by acquiring a new retail property in Ylivieska (between Vaasa and Oulu). The acquisition is made through a forward-funding structure with Wasagroup. Rental value of c. EUR 1.5M. The retail centre will be focusing on groceries and low-price retail, long term leases have been signed with Kesko and Rusta. Completion in 2026

Care home under development in Espoo, that upon completion will meet the Excellent requirements according to BREEAM and EPC A. Completion is scheduled for 2026. Once completed, the care home will be operated by Yrjö ja Hanna Hoivapalvelut under a 15-year lease agreeement. The care home will have 57 beds
JM has signed an agreement to sell a rental property project with 71 apartments in Helsinki. The deal amounts to c. SEK 205M. Construction started in Q1 2025 and completion is expected in Q2 2026.

column5: Investors House Oyj, Ovaro Kiinteistösijoitus Oyj
column11: Nordisk Renting a healthcare property in the Kukkumäki hospital area in Jyväskyla. The property consists of c. 17,600 sqm in across three buildings. It is fully leased to the regional wellbeing services authority under a triple-net lease until the end of 2041.

The City of Akaa has sold a fire station property located in Hirsikangas to Turku-based real estate developer KOy Amerin yritystalo. Built in 2013, the 1,100 sqm property is fully leased on a long-term contract to the Pirkanmaa Wellbeing Services County.

Evli Vuokratuotto has acquired a fully renovated retail property in Tuusula’s Hyrylä center from Staffia Oy. The property, previously vacant, was purchased by Staffia in December 2023 and redeveloped over 1.5 years. It now features Lidl and JYSK as anchor tenants, solar panels, and an energy storage system.
Ethos Capital acqured the W&T Avia property from Heino Group. The property is located adjacent to Tikkurilantie and in close proximity to both Tuusulanväylä and Ring III. It was completed in 2013.
Kielo has acquired a big box property in Tammisto, Vantaa. The leasable area is over 5,000 sqm and the largest tenant is Intersport.
Nyfosa divested the property Tuotekatu 7 in Reso, northwest of Turku. At the time of the divestment, the property had a negative operating income.

KSO has purchased an emptly plot of land in the centre of Kotka. The plot has been vacant since the demolition of Pohjolatalo in 2021. It is zoned for residential, office and commercial construction. Implementation could take place in 2026-2027, meaning construction could begin next year.

HUS has signed an LOI with Avara to potentially sell its Niemenmäki housing portfolio, comprising 424 staff apartments in western Helsinki. As part of the agreement, the future owner must commit to offering at least 400 units within 30 minutes of the Meilahti hospital for continued staff housing use.

The Vehkala Growth Lab, developed by Noste.io and built by Tekova, has been completed and acquired by VR Eläkesäätiö and the Industrial Union. The property is leased to Revenio Group Plc and ALS Finland.

Kojamo Oyj has agreed to sell a portfolio of 1,944 rental apartments spread across eight Finnish cities to Apollo and Avant Capital Partners for EUR 242M. The transaction includes 44 residential properties across eight cities. Annual revenue is c. EUR 21M.

Nordiqus has acquired two preschools from Sievi Hyvinvointitilat. The properties have a total lettable area of c. 2,000 sqm with capacity for just over 200 children. Both properties are fully leased to Peikkometsä Liikuntapäiväkoti on pure triple-net agreements, with a WAULT of c. 19.5 years and an annual rental value of EUR 500K. The Nurmijärvi preschool was completed in 2023, while the Träskända building is expected to be completed in July 2025.

Logian has agreed to purchase a logistics and production facility of approximately 15,000 sqm from TKU-Rakennus Oy in Raisio, Finland. The property, located along the Turku bypass road, will be constructed immediately and is expected to be completed by summer 2026. It has been leased under a long-term rental agreement to a large international company in the electrical and automation industry.

Aedifica has acquired a portfolio of six modern care properties across Finland for c. EUR 37.5M, with an initial yield over 6%. The portfolio includes three elderyly care homes and three group homes for people with intellectual disabilities, with a total of 233 residential spaces. The assets are operated by Attendo, Ikifit and Mehiläinen.

UrbanLight, a joint venture by Alma Property Partners and Alea Partners acquires a property with workshop and warehouse space. The 4,000 sqm property sits on a 36,000 sqm plot and was completed in 2020.

Logistea is purchasing a light industrial property in the MORE business area in Hämeenlinna. Annual rental income is c. EUR 2.05M and the lease agreement has c. 10 years remaining. The property is fully leased to Faerch Finland Oy.
The special investment fund UB Pohjoismaiset Liikekiinteistöt has sold a plot of land zoned for industrial or logistics use in Vantaa, near the intersection of Ring Road III and Tuusulanväylä.

A joint investment company of Aktiivtilat and Keva is purchasing a property located at Tikkurilantie 140 in Vantaa from Ilmarinen. The property has two separate logistics buildings. One of the buildings will be vacated at the end of the year, and the other is rented for food production.

Hartela has sold the Local Service Center Karjasillan Verstaan in Oulu to Balder Finland. The commercial property was completed in May 2025 and its tenants include Kesko, Fitness24seven and the Finnish Construction Federation.

Evli Fund Management Company has sold a portfolio consisting of seven warehouse and production properties to Balder Finland. The properties have a leasable area of ​​approximately 25,000 sqm, and they are located in Oulu, Pirkanmaa, Seinäjoki and Kuopio. Anchor tenants include global players such as Bosch Rexroth, Ahlsell and Dahl, as well as domestic companies such as Sukkamestarit, Tammermatic and Screentec.

Etson Holding has purchased a vacant office property located at Kappelikuja 4 in Niittykumpu, Espoo, from Sponda. The property has an area of ​​approximately 2,000 square meters. The buyers intend to transform the vacant premises into a destination that brings together electric bikes, travel and active lifestyle brands.

PPI has acquired two healthcare and community service properties in the Tikkurila district of Helsinki. The buildings, constructed in 2019 and 2021, span 13,520 sqm and are fully leased. One property is a specialist hospital with a 12-year lease to Mehiläinen. The other is a mixed-use property with tenants including Vantaa City, Forenom, Nordea, Terveystalo, and Kesko. The total annual gross rental income is approximately EUR 5.8M.

Helkama-Kiinteistöt, has acquired a 2,300 sqm production and office property in Tampere’s Vehmaiset district from BRAND toimitilat Oy. Completed in 2024, the property is fully leased to Adwatec Oy, a company specializing in liquid cooling systems for power electronics.
Evli’s development fund has sold two fully leased discount retail properties in Porvoo and Kotka. The tenants are under long-term contracts.

The City of Pori and the Satakunta Welfare Region have negotiated an LOI preparing the sale of the city hospital. The welfare district, which operates as a tenant, would purchase the city hospital from the city for EUR 36.5M.

SOK has sold the property complex in Jollas, Helsinki, which previously operated as the Jollas Institute and a hotel. The site includes over 40,000 sqm of land, buildings totaling more than 5,000 sqm, unused building rights, a private shoreline, and its own island.

Suomen Hallikiinteistöt I Oy, backed by Keva and Aktiivitilat, has acquired an 8,100 sqm logistics and industrial property in Kiviruukki, Espoo from Conficap Oy. The building, originally constructed in 1971 and 1982, features a mix of warehousing, wholesale, and service spaces, and is intended to remain in industrial use, with future value potential from zoning changes.

Plus Hoivakodit Oy, a JV between NREP and Plus Hoivakiinteistö, has acquired the Porvoo Hospital site for EUR 380K, outbidding the City of Porvoo. The 7,300 sqm plot will be investigated for redevelopment into a modern nursing home.

The City of Vantaa is acquiring three undeveloped plots from YIT in the Veromies district for EUR 2.5 million, adding 13,600 sqm of building rights to its land reserve. The plots have remained unused since being sold to YIT in 2000.  The city is planning, among other things, the Muura Park Bridge.

column4: Finedge Real Estate and Data Centre Oy
column11: The City of Lohja has sold the data center block area to Finedge Real Estate and Data Centre Oy, a subsidiary of Hyperco Oy. Hyperco confirmed that they currently have no negotiations or agreements with TikTok regarding the Lohja project.

The City of Salo has approved a preliminary agreement to sell 7 hectares of industrial land in the Kärkä area to Regant Oy. The purchase price is 50 euros per square meter of floor space, depending on the number of square meters of floor space to be implemented, with a minimum price of EUR 2.5M.  The final sale is contingent on conditions such as building permits and is expected to close within six months.

Northern Horizon has acquired two fully leased healthcare properties in Espoo and Lahti, Finland, from eQ Community Properties Fund. The 3,500 sqm portfolio is the first acquisition for Northern Horizon’s new Aged Care and Social Infrastructure Fund. Both properties are operated by Attendo under long-term, inflation-indexed leases.

JM has acquired residential building rights in Hannusranta, Espoo, in a transaction valued at SEK 99 million. The deal includes 190 units acquired directly and 290 through a joint arrangement with another buyer. The site has an approved zoning plan and will allow for the development of 480 homes, with construction expected to start in Q2 2026.

Nordisk Renting has acquired the Tipotie Social and Healthcare Centre (13,467 sqm) in Tampere from the City of Tampere, following a public tender. The building is fully leased to the Wellbeing Services County of Pirkanmaa under a 20-year lease.
Aktiivitilat, via its joint venture with Keva (Suomen Hallikiinteistöt Ky), has completed its second investment by acquiring a 4,800 sqm logistics property at Terästie 13 in the Ahjo area of Kerava.

Suomen Hallikiinteistöt Ky, the joint investment platform of Keva and Aktiivitilat, has made its first acquisition by purchasing a 1,500 sqm industrial property in Tuusula’s Jussla area. The asset is fully leased to a single tenant. The seller is a privately held property company.

Turun Osuuskauppa has acquired full ownership of Kauppakeskus Mylly in Raisio by purchasing the 50% stake previously owned by SOK. The two cooperative groups had jointly owned the centre through Kauppakeskus Mylly Oy since its establishment in 2001.

PPI has acquired a life science property under development in Otaniemi university campus area in Espoo. The property will be completed by the end of 2026. The total lettable area will be c. 15,700 sqm and it is fully pre-let on long-term lease agreements with an average unexpired leased term of over 10 years. Annual net operating income at completion is estimated to be c. EUR 4.9M.
A sale-and-leaseback transaction with a major grocery chain in Iisalmi. The property has a lettable area of c. 2,500 sqm and is fully leased on an 18-year lease agreement without break options.
Okartek sold its production and warehouse facilities in the Nummenniity industrial area in Kaarina. The facilities had a total area of 9,500 sqm,

column4: Tristan Capital Partners, Catella Asset Management
column11: EPISO 6, the joint venture between Tristan Capital Partners and Catella Asset Management has acquired a logistics centre in Espoo. The total leasable area is c. 21,000 sqm and has been leased entirely to Valio Aimo.

Logian, a joint venture between Mrec IM and Keva, has acquired an industrial and warehouse property of c. 10,000 sqm from the state-owned special purpose company Governia Oy. The property is located in Vantaa, right next to Helsinki-Vantaa airport. The purchase price is not disclosed.
HGR acquires a property in Otaniemi, Espoo from ACRE. The property is suitable for teaching, care or office use. The purchase price is not disclosed.
Sponda has sold its office property in Tampere to Tahoma Oy. The property is situated next to the Nokia Arena and offers 14,600 sqm of leasable area. The purchase price has not been disclosed.

Helsinki's Urban Environment Committee has dicussed the sale of the Uschakoff building on Pohjoisesplanadi to Cobbleyard. The office and commcercial building has a floor area of c. 3,400 sqm and is also known as the Kluuvi Government Office Building.
CBRE IM has sold the Skanssi shopping center in Turku to a fund managed by Swiss Life Asset Managers. The purchase price was not disclosed, however it is estimated to be in the range of EUR 90-100M.

Ovaro’s subsidiary, Jyväskylän Kukkulan Kehitys Oy, is selling part of the protected buildings located in the Kukkula area of Jyväskylä. Royal House Oy is purchasing three protected buildings from the company for a total sale price of €1.1 million. The combined floor area of the sold properties is approximately 4,500 square meters.

VVT is acquiring a commercial property located at Nilsaksentie 2, in the Tammisto retail cluster of Vantaa. The seller in the transaction is Pohjola Insurance. The purchase price has not been disclosed. Most of the building’s 10,000 square meters is leased to Tokmanni.

Avain Yhtiöt has purchased a plot of land in Vantaa's Aviapolis area on the corner of Tikkurilantie and Manttaalitie from pension insurance company Veritas. The purchase price is not disclosed. This is the largest single land acquisition in Avain Yhtiöt's history. The purchase concerns c. 43,000 sqm of building rights.

Senaatti-kiinteistöt has sold the Kuopio barracks block area and its buildings to Rakennustyö Salminen Oy and its parent company, the property development company Stockpos Oy. The sold area is located in central Kuopio, on a plot between Puistokatu and Hatsalankatu. The area includes four protected barracks buildings and 4,760 square meters of new residential building rights.

Ragde Eiendom has sold a portfolio of three retail properties in Espoo, Porvoo and Vaasa. The properties have a combined leasable area of c. 13,500 sqm and have previously operated as Plantagen stores. Plantagen in Finland filed for bankruptcy las autumn.

The City of Helsinki has purchased an office building from Sponda at Tallinnanaukio in Itäkeskus, a district in eastern Helsinki. The property is a five-story office and commercial building, completed in 1985, with a floor area of approximately 4,500 square meters.

Niam has puchased a newly built hotel and residential property in central Helsinki from Ylva. The hotel building houses Citybox's first hotel in Finland, with 178 rooms and a total lettable area of c. 7,200 sqm. The residential building offers 57 apartments and a total lettable area of 2,500 sqm.
Onvest has sold two business premises. The properties are located in Koivuhaka, Vantaa, and in Herttoniemi, Helsinki.

A. Ahlström Properties acquired an office complex under construction in Central Pasila from Avain Yhtiöt. The area has previously been used as a railway yard. The office section offers office space for up to 450 employees. Construction began early 2025, and the office building is expectd to be completed by the end of 2026.

NREP has entered into a strategic joint venture focused on the Finnish care home market with Plus Hoivakiinteistöt. The joint venture will cover development and operation of the homes, with EUR 400M allocated for investment over the next three years. The development of initial 11 care homes - valued at EUR 70M - is scheduled to begin this year. Negotiations are ongoing for more than EUR 100M worth of further projects.

NCC is divesting the public properties project Cleantech Garden to Suohki, which is wholly owned by Infranode. The properties have a total lettable area of 13,750 sqm, with The City of Espoo as the largest tenant with a new school. The transaction was based on a property value of approximately SEK 900M.

HGR Property Partners has sold a development project to PPI. The transaction covers a school and daycare property in Kruununhaka, Helsinki. The property has a lettable area of c. 5,000 sqm and is fully leased under long-term agreements.  The project involves extensive renovation and repurposing of an existing building in Kruununhaka, which will house a daycare for the City of Helsinki and a private school.

Stendörren has purchased a light industrial property located at Martinkyläntie 52 in Varisto, Vantaa along with a property in Copenhagen. The purchase price of both properties amounted to SEK 92M with a total area of 10,500 sqm.

Redeve Oy's subsidiary Kansallisholding Oy and the City of Kristiinankaupunki have signed a pre-reservation agreement for an area of approx. 235 hectares. After the pre-reservation agreement, the area will be zoned for data center use in coorporation with the city. The area will enable the construction of the largest, so-called hyperscale, data center.

Bolivo Bostad, in partnership with Altaal and Avant Capital Partners, has completed their first acquisition in Finland. The have acquired 142 rental apartments spread across three properties in Espoo.
Verne has purchased an eight-hectare plot of land from Onvest with plans to increase the capacity of its data centre to 70 megawatts.

The City of Porvoo and HUS have negotiated the sale of the property in the Porvoo Hospital area. The property comprises of approx. 7,300 sqm land and includes buildings that are ready for demolition. The building rights on the plot are approx. 1,830 sqm. In the zoning plan the area is zoned for social services and healthcare buildings, and residential buildings.

AMF is selling its 33.3% stake in Mercada Oy to Kesko. Mercada owns 35 properties across Finland. The portfolio has a leasable area of c. 290,000 sqm, consisting mainly of grocery stores leased to Kesko and the shopping centers Karisma and Veturi.

OP Bank Group has sold two commercial properties to HOK-Elanto. The properties are located in Juvanmalmi, Espoo and Vuosaari, Helsinki. HOK-Elanto is the main user of both the properties. The property in Juvanmalmi has an area of c. 2,200 sqm and the property in Vuosaari has an area of c. 2,400 sqm.

Pontos Group has sold a total of four properties from its real estate portfolio. The total area of the divested properties was over 23,000 square meters and included logistics and commercial properties. The properties were located in various towns across Finland.The properties were sold one by one, mainly to domestic private investors.

The special investment fund Evli Logistiikkakiinteistöt has acquired two industrial properties located in Hämeenlinna. This is a two-phase transaction, the first phase of which was completed in January of last year.

UB Asuntorahasto I Ky has made its first investments. In January, the fund purchased a total of 38 apartments and 29 parking spaces in Helsinki, Espoo, and Kauniainen. The apartments are completed between 2017 and 2023, located in central areas along rail transport routes.

Jatke Länsi-Suomi has purchased the former Petrea rehabilitation center property from Kela, located in the Petrelius area of Turku. The property has been completely vacant since the end of 2016. The property covers approximately 30,000 square meters and the deal includes a 5.8-hectare land area, which is currently being zoned. The area is planned to include housing.

Julius Tallberg-Kiinteistöt has sold the property it owns at Tapulikaupungintie 37 in Suutarila, Helsinki, to another investor. Kiinteistö Oy Suutarilan Huoltokeskus is an office and warehouse property that is fully leased to Ramirent Finland Oy. The property has long served as Ramirent’s Finnish headquarters as well as a service point and warehouse for construction equipment rental.

column5: Tampereen Tornit Ky (LähiTapiola, OP, Ilmarinen and SRV)
column11: A joint venture owned by LähiTapiola, OP, Ilmarinen, and SRV, Tampereen Tornit Ky, has announced the sale of Kiinteistö Oy Kansi ja Areena Pysäköinti (Tampere Kansi Arena parking facility) to a fund managed by the German AIF Capital Group.

The property serves as Ahlsell’s central warehouse in Finland. Ahlsell has leased the property since its construction in 2002. Fully-let, WAULT 15 years and NOI €3.6 million. Yield ~6%. The lettable area includes 10,856 sqm of open storage.

The Norwegian real estate company Public Property Invest ASA (PPI), listed on the Oslo Stock Exchange, has signed an agreement to acquire two adjacent school properties in Espoo. This is the company’s first investment in Finland. Mrec Investment Management acts as PPI’s local operating partner in Finland. The total area of the properties acquired by PPI in Espoo is approximately 10,000 square meters, and they are fully leased. 94 percent of the area is leased to the City of Espoo. The annual gross rental income is approximately 2.93 million euros, and the average remaining lease term is 14 years. Yield some 5.3%

The municipality of Nurmijärvi has sold the fire station property in the central area of Nurmijärvi. The buyer was a real estate company owned by local entrepreneurs. The asset is entirely leased to the Vantaa and Kerava Welfare Area.

Kansallis-yhtiöt and Käpyrinne ry have completed the transaction at Ilmattarentie 2, Käpylä. The property will be converted for supported housing use under a long-term lease agreement with the City of Helsinki. The property will have 67 residential places and facilities for related support services.

The special investment fund eQ Community Properties has agreed with Ilmarinen on a real estate transaction and Ilmarinen’s investment in the same fund. The fund will purchase four properties from Ilmarinen, located in Helsinki, Espoo, and Vantaa. The tenants of the properties are the City of Helsinki, the City of Vantaa, the Western Uusimaa Welfare Area, and Aimo Park. At the same time, Ilmarinen has made an investment in the fund, which was completed on December 31."
The city of Kuusamo has sold the Kuusamo Health Center and the Ruijanmutka Group Home to a private investor.

Keva and Osuuskauppa Arina have agreed on the sale of shares in Kiinteistö Oy Rovaniemen Pohjanpuistikko. The real estate company owns the building where Arina’s Original Sokos Hotel Vaakuna Rovaniemi operates. Until now, the hotel has been a tenant of Keva in the property.
Ilmarinen has sold a car dealership property located in Limingantulli, Oulu. The buyer was Jarmo Rinta-Jouppi’s real estate company Park Invest Oy. The property houses a Rinta-Jouppi store.

Toivo Group has signed agreements with a fund managed by NREP for two social infrastructure properties. One of the properties is a facility for Esperi Care Oy in Kangasala, with preparatory construction work already underway. The other property will be for the elderly and will be built in Helsinki. The goal is to start construction of the Helsinki facility during 2025.

Altaal has acquired prime office building Fab 9 located in Helsinki CBD. The seller, KanAm acquired the property from Genesta in 2022 for 3.15% yield. Now, the asset traded for 5.7% yield. Krogerus, a leading law firm, occupies ca 70% of the building.
Develo Toimitilat Oy is purchasing a retail property located in Tammisto, Vantaa, which was previously used by Plantagen. Plantagen Finland filed for bankruptcy in September.
Majakkalahden Kiinteistöt Oy sold a residential portfolio consisting of a total of 185 apartments. The properties are located in Oulu, Jyväskylä, Kuopio, and Rovaniemi.

Previously, the logistics center was intended to be sold through a sale and leaseback arrangement. However, the Ministry of Social Affairs and Health issued a preliminary statement on the sale, which changed the plans. According to the Organization Act, a welfare area can only transfer a social and healthcare facility or property if it is included in the ministry-approved social and healthcare sub-plan. Joint Authority Board also decided to initiate the tendering of warehouse operations. The terms of the request for proposals require the selected bidder to lease the sold warehouse property until the end of the lease term. Based on initial information, the yield would be 6.5% (NOI €0.72m).

Henki-Fennia sells a well-known medical center property in Munkkivuori, Helsinki, to a fund managed by the French company Corum. The property is Pihlajalinna Dextra Munkkivuori, located at Raumantie 1a. The property has been part of Henki-Fennia’s real estate investment portfolio, managed by S-Pankki Kiinteistöt.

Toivo Group Oyj has sold a portfolio of three residential apartment buildings comprising 240 apartments to Sirius Capital Partners for approx. 35 million euros. The buildings are completed between 2021 and 2023.

UrbanLight continues to expand its light industrial and logistics portfolio by acquiring two light industrial properties located in Jussla, Tuusula. The transaction is a sale and leaseback with Kreate Group.

HPP assists the subsidiary of the real estate investment company Trophi Fastighets AB in a sale and leaseback arrangement, through which it acquires a commercial property located in Munkinmäki, Kirkkonummi. A development project is underway on the target property, where a grocery store building is being constructed. The building will be leased to a grocery store operator under a long-term lease agreement

Group of investors have acquired the voting C-series shares of Helsinki Halli Oy (former Hartwall Arena). The voting shares of the arena company were sold to a Finnish buyer group led by the real estate investment company Trevian. The transaction still requires approval from authorities and an EU-level exemption.

Stora Enso has signed an agreement to sell the Sunila property in Kotka to AALTO Development Oy. The transaction is expected to be completed by the end of this year. The parties have agreed not to disclose the sale price. AALTO Development aims to transform Sunila into a hub for sustainable energy transition technology, including significant investments in Gen-H Oy’s hydrogen-based solutions.

column5: Elite Finland Value Added Fund II Ky
column11: Elite Finland Value Added Fund II Ky has sold a warehouse and retail property located in Seppälä, Jyväskylä, to a private domestic investor. The entire property is leased to Kesko Oyj under a long-term lease agreement.

Conficap has sold a office property located at Vetotie 3 in Kaivoksela, Vantaa. The building is particularly known as the current headquarters of Sustera. Sustera will move to Pitäjänmäki, Helsinki, in January 2025.

UrbanLight, a joint venture established last year by Alma Property Partners and Alea Partners, acquires two properties near Helsinki-Vantaa Airport. The larger of the acquired properties, Tikkurilantie 154, includes approximately 22,000 square meters of logistics space. The property is fully leased to DB Schenker.
Balder Finland acquired a LI/retail property located in Kirkkonummi. The asset is almost fully leased to Wurth and Autoklinikka. 2024 Estimated NOI some €0.2m and WAULT 4 years.

column5: Mandatum AM Suomi Kiinteistöt II, SSA Rakennus Oy, n.a.
column11: Cibus has through three separate transactions acquired three grocery stores in Finland. The properties hold 100% daily-goods with WAULT of 12.9 years. The first acquired property (price €4.2m) is leased to S Group and the third acquired property was built in 2024 and is leased to Kesko. No detailed information regarding the second transaction is disclosed.
FinCap's data center company buys two properties and land of some 10 hectares located in Lahti. The current premises are mainly in logistics and warehouse use. The price is not disclosed.
Day-care asset built in 2024. After the acquisition, Kinland has almost 190 assets in Finland. Because the seller doesn't want any publicity, the available information is very limited.

Lumme Palvelukiinteistöt, a Finnish real estate investment company focusing on care properties, has acquired a portfolio of eight care properties for approximately 30 million euros from Hoivarakentajat Oy. Lumme is a jointly owned by Alma Property Partners and senior members of the operating team. The company’s goal is to build a care property portfolio exceeding 100 million euros.
The property, located at Kalliotie 2, is Tuusula Business Center. The asset is fully leased. Yield some 9%. Constructed 1968-2003.

column5: The Wellbeing Services County of Pirkanmaa
column11: The municipality will purchase the former hospital area of Kaivanto from Wellbeing Services County. The purchase price is 530,000 euros. The total area includes 21.3 hectares and seven properties with buildings. The buildings will be demolished during 2025, and the area will be developed in the coming years.

column4: The Wellbeing Services County of Kanta-Häme
column11: The Wellbeing Services County acquired hospital properties located in Forssa. According to Oma Häme, one of Oma Häme’s three social and health service centers will be located in Forssa Hospital.

Varte Oy and Hoivatilat Oyj have finalized a transaction in Jaakkola, Kerava. A new daycare building was completed at Palopellonkatu 6 B in May 2024. Varte Lahti Oy served as the main contractor for the project.

column4: Ethos Light Industrial Strategies I Ky
column11: Ethos Light Industrial Strategies I Ky fund, managed by Finnish real estate investment company Ethos Capital, has acquired two additional properties. One of the properties, which includes warehouse, logistics, and production space, is located near Kehä III in Espoo and covers an area of approximately 2,200 square meters. The other property is situated in Kerava and spans around 2,350 square meters.
S-Pankki Toimitila Special Investment Fund has sold a production and logistics property that it has owned for a long time in Piispankylä, Vantaa, at the address Mestaritie 8.

Ifolor group has sold its production property located in Kerava to a private real estate investor. In spring, Ifolor announced its decision to concentrate its production operations in Switzerland, where the company’s headquarters and larger production unit are located.
An off-market deal, no news published. Mileway already has several properties within the close area.
An off-market deal, no news published. The tenant PNO is heavy equipment trailer rental company, and their trailer center is located on the property.

Logistics property near the airport in Aviapolis, Vantaa. The property is designed for storing products requiring special temperature conditions and was completed in 2018. The property is fully let to grocery wholesaler Wihuri. CBRE was advisor

Three healthcare and hospital properties. The transaction includes two properties acquired from eQ Social Properties special investment fund in the centre of Helsinki and one in central Pori. The largest tenants are Docrates, Mehiläinen and Terveystalo. JLL and Catella were advisors

Logian has acquired two logistics properties in Tuusula from funds managed by OP Real Estate Asset Management. The properties are located some 3 km north-east of Helsinki-Vantaa airport and the premises are fully leased to Logitri Oy. The buyer is a joint venture between Keva and Mrec Investment Management Oy.

A light industrial portfolio comprising 22 light industrial assets. The Helsinki region contributes 77% to the portfolio's NOI, while the remaining 23% comes from the assets in Tampere. Yield 8.09% on Seller's NOI including rental guarantees and 7.72% on Seller's NOI excluding rental guarantees.

The property is located in the city centre of Oulu, and it is occupied by anchor tenant Mehiläinen Oy, covering over 74% of the gross rental income. The property is consructed in 2015, occupancy rate is 98% and the NOI is some €2.8m

Sirius Capital Partners has acquired two residential properties from OP Vuokratuotto - a special investment fund. The properties consist of a total of 158 apartments. The properties are located in Etelä-Haaga and Pasila. One of the buildings is in energy class A, and Sirius plans to upgrade the other one from energy class B to A by installing solar panels.

Innovestor Real Estate has invested in a new commercial property in Tuupakka, Vantaa, along Ring Road 3, at the address Kalliosolantie 4. The property is designed and developed to meet the needs of the real estate services company Lassila & Tikanoja Oyj.

Funds managed by Slättö have, through two separate transactions, agreed to acquire two residential portfolios in Finland, for a total transaction value of EUR 130 million. The acquisitions are made with Finnish institutional investors as co-investors. 70 per cent of the value is concentrated in the HMA and the residential portfolios comprise approximately 800 residential units.

Bus company Väinö Paunu Oy has sold the former bus depot building located in Nekala, Tampere. According to buyer, the property has plenty of unused building right, making the acquisition an excellent fit for their project development and growth strategy. The premises will be renovated to meet modern requirements. The building was constructed in the 1950s.

Nurminen Logistics Oyj is selling a 51% majority stake in the shares of Kiinteistöosakeyhtiö Helsingin Satamakaari 24 to Ilmarinen. This stake represents Nurminen’s ownership in the company’s headquarters and terminal property located in Vuosaari, Helsinki. As a result of the deal, full ownership of the property will transfer to Ilmarinen, which previously held a 49% stake. The existing lease agreement for the property will continue for five years from the date of the transaction.

Cityvarasto Oyj has acquired the shares entitling ownership of a commercial space located at Hämeenkatu 66 in the center of Hyvinkää. A modern self-storage hotel will be opened in the premises by the end of the year.

OP-Vuokratuotto real estate fund divested a light industrial property located at Kivikonlaita 25 in Kivikko, Helsinki. The fund acquired the property from its user in November 2019. The asset was constructed in 2009 and it has lettable area of 6,400 sq m, NOI €0.86m and WAULT 10.7 years.

Balder Finland is acquiring a portfolio of four production and commercial properties in Finland. The anchor tenants in these properties include Havator, Lassila & Tikanoja, EFC Finland, and Volvo Construction Equipment.

The portfolio comprises of four properties (243 apartments) and the value is approximately 50 million euros. The buildings have been recently completed between 2021 and 2022. This is the fund’s first investment in Finland.

Niitty is a shopping center completed in 2017, which also includes a metro station. The largest operator in Niitty is the HOK-Elanto S-market. Cushman & Wakefield acted as the seller's advisor, the purchase price was not disclosed. NOI €1.71m and technical occupancy 96.5%.

Toivo Group has signed a contract package in which the company will deliver a family housing portfolio of about 140 apartments to Nuveen Real Estate. The portfolio consists of detached houses, semi-detached houses, and row house properties. The portfolio includes one completed property and three properties under construction, located in Helsinki, Espoo, and Vantaa. The value of the contract is approximately 41.85 million euros.

Premico Residential Fund III and construction service company Fira have agreed on the construction of a high-quality rental apartment building in Postipuisto, Helsinki. The complex will consist of 99 apartments and the project is expected to be completed in summer 2025. Cushman & Wakefield advised the seller.

Niam and Kuuskodit Investment Management announced the launch of a new joint venture, an initiative to enhance family living through the development of terraced family houses, tailored for the rental market in the Finish growth triangle HMA, Tampere and Turku. The joint venture has acquired a seed portfolio, comprising five assets with 117 apartments, built in 2021-2022.

The Leschehemmet Foundation sold its property located at Huvilakatu 3. The building was completed in 1910 and the original purpose of the building was residential apartments, but it was converted into a senior services home in the 1950s. Last summer, the city of Helsinki approved a zoning decision that allows the building to revert from a senior services home back to residential apartments.
Oy Wasa ST-Invest Ltd has divested light industrial property in Mustasaari, some 10km from Vaasa city centre.

Senaatti-kiinteistöt has sold an office and laboratory property located at Tietotie 2 in Espoo’s Otaniemi to Aalto University. The complex was built in several phases starting from the 1960s. The property was previously used by VTT Technical Research Centre of Finland, but their operations ceased in the fall of 2023, leaving the premises vacant. Tietotie 2 is part of the Biologi zoning area, which is planned to accommodate a variety of university functions, housing, and services.

The property was built in 2006. It is a fully leased logistics property, and the current tenant, Schenker, has been operating there for 10 years. The property was part of the ReLog portfolio, which Pontos acquired from NREP in the spring of 2019.

The Bredis retail park was completed in two parts in 2019 and 2021. The complex, consisting of four properties, has a total area of approximately 23,000 square meters. Tenants include Lidl, Rusta, Tokmanni, Power, Jysk, and Puuilo.
As a result of the transaction, the buyer gains control over more than 500 parking spaces in the P-Louhi parking facility located in Turku.
column18: Capman Acquires Logistics Asset at Turku Airport | Nordic Property News

column11: Cromwell European REIT has divested office property located in Kielotie 7, Vantaa.
column18: JM Finland bought nokia manor and plans apartments for 1,500 residents | Building Leaf (www-rakennuslehti-fi.translate.goog)

column11: The assets is on a freehold plot and the building is constructed during the 1970s and 1980s. The most recent renovations were carried out in the 2020s. The tenants include, among others, Tokmanni, Lidl, and Forenom Hostel. Current occupancy some 60% and yield around 13%. Cerberus bought the asset from Citycon in 2017.
Local real estate developer acquired a shopping center from Pontos. Current occupancy rate over 90%. The asset was part of the ReLog portfolio that was acquired from NREP in 2019.

The portfolio consists of four properties and 251 apartments, with a total leaseable area of approximately 10,000 square meters. The properties are completed between 2021 and 2023. According to Sirius, the company's goal is to build a residential portfolio worth approximately €500 million from recently completed properties.

column4: UrbanLight (Alma Property Partners and Alea Partners)
column11: Off-market deal in Koivuhaka, Vantaa. The premises are leased to tenants such as Skanska Rakennuskone and Pakkauspörssi. Second acquisition for UrbanLight.
High quality light industrial asset in Tampere with excellent location. 10-year WAULT. Initial yield 8.4%

Cityvarasto Oyj has acquired a property in Mikkeli, located at Yrittäjänkatu 10, on its own approximately 2,600 square meter plot. The property has a building right of 1,537 square meters. A modern self-storage hotel will be opened on the property by the end of the year.

Kesko has acquired two properties from the eQ Commercial Properties fund: the Sinikallio Shopping Center (10,400 sqm) located in Mankkaa, Espoo, and the K-Citymarket (9,400 sqm) in Salo. Kesko has been the main tenant and primary user in both properties for an extended period.

The building project pertaining the expansion of the now approximately 3,000 sqm commercial building located on the property was finalized late in 2023. The building is leased with a long-term lease agreement to a well-known Finnish retailer.
Off-market deal in Tampere city center, Hämeenkatu 24. The seller Huoneisto Kaksikko Oy is owned by Pentti Välkki.
Vantaanportti Retail Park consists of three commercial buildings. The property was built in 2002. NOI €2.6m, WAULT 3.8 years and occupancy rate 99%. Anchored by Lidl.

The approximately 14,000 sqm project, which will be constructed for Terveystalo, is set to begin immediately, with tenant planning to move into the new premises by the summer of 2027. Hartela is the developer and builder of the project. The acquisition price is not disclosed.

Cobbleyard Real Estate has divested Niittytie 12 in Vantaa. The divested property is a last-mile warehouse with 6,400 sqm let to one tenant on a long lease. The divestment is Cobbleyard's third transaction in 12 weeks.

column4: UrbanLight (Alma Property Partners and Alea Partners)
column11: The property is located at Högbergintie 4 on a three-hectare plot, and there is approximately 2,500 square meters of leaseable area. The premises are entirely leased to BIMU Oy, a company specialized in environmental services. The deal seems to be sale-and-leaseback.

The property completed for Berner's use in 2009 consists of two buildings, with a total leaseable area of approximately 39,000 square meters. The property is fully leased to three tenants. The purchase price is not disclosed.

Elo has acquired two residential buildings from the Paavo Nurmi Foundation in Töölö and Kallio in Helsinki. The buildings were constructed in 1938 and 1912, and they have undergone extensive renovations over the years. In total, there are 94 apartments and 7 retail premises.
The light industrial and warehouse property, constructed in 1971, has 61% occupancy, 3.08 WAULT, and NOI of €320k (1.4.2023). The property is located some 1.5km from Kuopio city center.

Helkama-Kiinteistöt Oy has acquired a production and office property in Vehkala, Vantaa from JHM Invest Group Oy. The property was completed in 2019 and has approximately 2,620 sqm of leaseable area. The property is fully leased to Assa Abloy Entrance Systems.

The building was constructed in 1847 and currently it stands vacant. It has been identified with an indoor air quality issue, and its utilization will require extensive and costly repairs. Instead of selling the land, a 40-year lease agreement will be signed for it. Aare Invest’s intention is to renovate the building for business premises and potentially include restaurant or café spaces that would also be open to the general public.

column4: CapMan Nordic Real Estate III fund
column11: The Seminaari school property consists of eight buildings, all built at different times between 1930 and 1984. The property is leased by the City of Hämeenlinna under a long-term lease. Attached to the property and as part of the acquired asset is also an unbuilt plot, designated for residential use in the master plan. CapMan Real Estate has agreed with the City of Hämeenlinna to discuss development opportunities for the plot.

VVT has acquired a modern office property located at Vuolteenkatu 2 in Tampere. The property is almost fully let and its largest tenant is Elisa. The building is completed in 2020 and it is LEED Gold certified and has energy class rating A. CBRE acted as the seller's advisor. WAULT 5.2 years, NOI €3.2m.

Etelä-Pohjanmaan hyvinvointialue acquired 80% of the premises that are under construction in Seinäjoki. The acquired premises are made for social and healthcare use. The price is including the land that was acquired from the City of Seinäjoki. The deal was made in late 2023 and the estimated completion of the construction is in late 2024.
The office building is constructed in 2017. Kaleva will move their premises to Oulu city centre as the new owner will move in during the summer 2024.

column4: Ethos Capital (Ethos Light Industrial Strategies I Ky)
column11: The fund made its first acquistions in the summer of 2023. In December, the fund made its latest acquisitions by acquiring two ligh industrial porperties located in Kerava. The assets are leased to large international companies.

The City of Helsinki is selling Vallila Primary School building to Hemsö as a sale and leaseback deal. Hemsö and the City of Helsinki will sign a 20-year lease agreement regarding the school’s 3,500 square meters. The estimated renovation costs of the building is 16 million euros. The land is owned by the City and is going to be leased to Hemsö.
The acquisition is Slättö’s second in the hospitality sector in Finland. The office building will be converted to aparthotel use (99 hotel apartments). Bob W is Slättö's partner in the project.
The seller will continue as a tenant in the historical building for the next two years. Newsec acted as the seller's advisor.

As their first investment, Capman Social Real Estate fund acquires two daycare properties and one school property from HGR Property Partners. WAULT 21+ years. The fund aims to build a diversified portfolio that includes social real estate in Sweden, Finland, Denmark and Norway. The fund invests in properties such as healthcare, education and municipal services.
The property is located 5km from the Turku city centre. The premises are leased to life science company Revvity.
The two newly built daycare properties are leased to City of Oulu and City of Rovaniemi with long lease agreements.
In 1998 built storage proprety is located in Aviapolis, Vantaa. The premises are leased to 3stepIT. NOI is approximately 557k€ and WAULT 3 years.
All properties are leased 100% to Posti with triple net leases. In addition, there is 72,000sqm of unused building right. Yield ~6.4%.

The preschool properties are located in several different parts of Finland. Closing of the deal will be in Q1/2024. It was announced earlier in December that Kinland bought three daycare properties from UB Suomi Kiinteistöt.
LocalTapiola Aluekiinteistöt Ky acquired a portfolio of three retail properties from eQ Liikekiinteistöt. Main tenants are Kesko and Tokmanni.
Aare Invest Oy is developing new warehouse, logistics and production premises on the property. The lettable area of the divested premises is approximately 11,000 sqm.
The property consists of commercial and car repair premises and it is located in Hatanpää, approximately 1.5 km from the city centre.

column4: JM-Suomi Oy and LähiTapiola Tontit II Ky
column11: The sale of the property was preceded by planning and zoning development, which now enables residential construction. The ownership rights will be transferred and purchase price will be paid in the Q4/2024.

Senate Properties and Tuusula have signed a transaction for the central block of Rykmentinpuisto 1, Tuusula. In the area, a wellness center suitable for the needs of the Uusimaa well-being area is being planned.

column6: Helsinki region and other major cities
column11: NREP is acquiring a portfolio of 17 care properties from the eQ Yhteiskuntakiinteistöt. The portfolio includes units for assisted living, supported housing, and early childhood education across Finland. JLL acted as the seller's commerical advisor in the transaction.

column4: Fund managed by Catella Residential Investment Management
column11: The residential portfolio of 5 properties comprises 350 apartments with a total of 14,200 sqm of lettable area. The properties are completed between 2017 and 2021. JLL acted as the seller's advisor.

Innovestor Real Estate invests in a commercial property in Vantaa Varisto, located at Martinkyläntie 59. The modern property has been developed by UM Kiinteistöt and Tekova, which also served as the project’s contractor. Main tenants are Puuilo, Saka and Hiekka Beach Volley Club.
Tokmanni sells the Moreeni logistics center to Logicenters and leases it back with a 20-year lease agreement. The construction work of the newly built logistic center was completed in late 2023.

column4: Cobbleyard Real Estate and HCP Bricks
column11: Cobbleyard Real Estate and HCP Bricks Real Estate Fund are purchasing a historically significant property located at Eerikinkatu 32–36 in Kamppi from Kojamo. Next year, a significant renovation and energy investment will be carried out on the property.

UB Suomi Kiinteistöt has agreed to sell three daycare properties to a Nordic institutional investor. All these properties have Pilke Daycare as the tenant. The daycare properties were sold at their fair values.

Northern Horizon has acquired portfolio of 15 care home properties from eQ Yhteiskuntakiinteistöt. The properties have been leased to leading private companies in the field and are located in the Helsinki metropolitan area and other major cities. The total lettable area of the properties is nearly 20,000 square meters.
Auratum's fund divests a property in Tuusula. The lettable area of the buildings is approximately 4,000 sqm. The premises will be leased to Lidl and JYSK.
Lähitapiola Aluekiinteistöt Ky has acquired an office property near the center of Oulu. The property was completed in September and it is currently fully leased.

column4: Newil & Bau Oy and Kusinkapital Ab
column11: Newil & Bau and Kusinkapital have purchased two properties in Otaniemi, Espoo. The buildings have previoulsy been used for office, laboratory and teaching purposes. The new owners aim to develop the block for residential use and bring daycare and playgrounds to the area.
Croisette Real Estate Partner acted as commercial adviser to Mileway in the acquisition of a logistics property in Vantaa. The property is fully let to UPS Finland.

Kesko has purchased two plots in the city of Lahti. Kesko intends to use the purchased plots to build a new hypermarket with some total area of 9,500 sqm. The existing retail building will be demolished in 2023-2024.

Sagax has acquired one property in Finland and one property in the Netherlands in two separate transactions. The properties have a total lettable area of 16,900 square meters, mainly consisting of premises for warehouse and industrial purposes. Closing of the Finnish property has taken place during the Q4 2023 (11.8 MEUR).
HOK-Elanto (S Group) acquires two properties in the Helsinki region for EUR 9 million which is consistent with the reported property value.

CapMan Hotels II fund has signed an agreement to acquire the asset in Oulu city centre, with the intention of redeveloping the building, currently used as an office, into part of Lapland Hotels Oulu. The acquisition is expected to close and the redevelopment to start in one years’ time once required official authorisations have been obtained.

North European Invest Oy (owner of Lapland Hotels) acquires Vuoristö-Yhtiöt Oy which is the owner of oprations and real estates of a hotel Haikon Kartano. GLA 14,000 sqm, land area 150,000 sqm and water area 60,000 sqm. Haikon Kartano opened in 1966 and has 211 rooms.
OP-Henkivakuutus divest a warehouse property in Vantaa (Tuupakka). Buyer is not disclosed.  GLA 14,300 sqm. Anchor tenants are Neele-Vat Finland Oy and Boreo Oyj.
DEAS Property Fund Finland I divests an office property in Oulu (Aeroportti, Tietotie 2).

DEAS Asset Management has won a competition to develop the area of "Kätilöopisto" (maternity hospital area closed in 2018). The target is to develop a modern, inclusive and dark green residential area. Building right of approx. 30,000 sqm for residential, retail and public services use.

JM Suomi and Icecapital Housing Fund VI Ky have signed an agreement on the development of a residential property in Espoo (Finnoo). The property will have 8 floors and comprise 58 rental apartments. Expected completion in spring 2025.

Sato acquires an unstructured plot in Viikki, Helsinki. The city plan allows residential and commercial use. Plot area is 9,437 sqm. Helsinki City Board has not yet granted approval for the proposed detailed plan change.
Innovestor Real Estate acquires a new office property in Helsinki (Herttoniemi). The seller is a development company Tekova. Anchor tenants are Aqva Finland and Aide Europe. GLA 1,500 sqm.
Fennia acquires an office property in Helsinki (Länsi-Pasila) from YIT. Anchor tenant Eezy Oyj. GLA 12,400 sqm. Construction year 1987, fully refurbished in 2023. Fully let NOI €3.3m.
Ovaro acquires an office property in Jyväskylä from Sijoitusasunnot.com. Yield 14%. Construction year 1977, renovated 2002.

column5: Svenska Lutherska Evangeliföreningen i Finland r.f
column11: Svenska Lutherska Evangeliföreningen i Finland r.f. divested a property in Espoo (Koskelo). Buyer not disclosed. Value-add property, currently leased to a single tenant until the end of 2023.

VVT acquires logistics property from OP-Vuokratuotto special investment fund. The property is located 5 km north of Helsinki airport and has LEED Gold certification. The tenant is Logitri, with a WAULT of 9 years. The construction year is 2021. NOI €1.47m.

Kesko acquires majority of shares of a grocery-anchored local retail center in Espoo centre from Cerberus Capital Management. In-place NOI €1.7m (May 2023). Rezoning for hypermarket extension ongoing. Managed by Cromwell.

Niam acquired a landmark property in Kamppi, Helsinki from the City of Helsinki. NOI €2.2m, yield 7.33%. 80% vendor note, 4% interest. Anchor tenant is a cinema chain Finnkino. The property was built in 1937. Transaction is conditional on the approval of the Helsinki Urban Environment Committee.
UB Suomi Kiinteistöt acquired a grocery store property in Oulu from Technocampus. The property was completed in 2021 and is fully let to Kesko on a long-term lease.
Genesta’s value-add fund GNRE Fund 3 acquires “Voimatalo”, an office property in Kamppi in Helsinki, from Schroder Real Estate KVG. The property is let to 13 tenants

Niam acquires an office property “Sampotalo” in Turku city centre from Schroder Nordic Real Estate Fund. GLA 10,400. All office spaces have been leased to City of Turku under a long lease agreement. The property has also some ground level retail premises. The property was built in 1937-1938 and was designed by architect Erik Bryggman to serve as insurance company Sampo's HQ.

Hoivatilat acquires four new development care properties from Vestera. Properties are located in HMA, Lahti, Turku and Tampere. Three of the properties are special housing service units and one is a kindergarten. Scheduled completions before summer 2024.

NREP acquires share of a shopping centre property located in Kauniainen from special investment fund Evli Vuokratuotto II. NREP acquired a first share of the property in December 2022 from VVT Kiinteistösijoitus.

Slättö acquires a hotel property located in central Helsinki from private investors. The property will be refurbished with a new operator Bob W and will be certified under the environmental scheme LEED. Expected opening during 2024.

Hoivatilat acquires a new development day care property from WasaGroup. The property will be fully let to City of Tuusula, WAULT 20 years. Construction begins in August 2023. Scheduled completion in August 2024.

column4: Pohjola Rakennus & Elo Mutual Pension Insurance Company
column11: A consortium led by Pohjola Rakennus and Elo Mutual Pension Insurance Company has a acquired an uncostructured plot in Herttoniemi, Helsinki. The city plan allows residential and commercial use.

Naim acquires a new office property in Hakaniemi with substantial ESG credentials, including energy performance rating A and LEED Platinum. Largest tenant is IBM. WAULT of 5.4 years, estimated fully let NOI €2.9m.
Fully-let fffice property in Keilaniemi, Espoo. The property is built in 2001 and serves as TietoEvry's headquarter

Microsoft acquires site for a future data centre. The planned data centre is in Vihti's Rosti Business Park, and will consist of three separate and independently operating data centres that are synchronised with each other. The total land area is c. 46 hectares
A fund managed by Slättö acquires a last-mile logistics property in Tattariharju, Helsinki. Price and seller are not disclosed.

column5: OP Public Services Real Estate Fund
column11: Kinland acquires 15 social infrastructure properties across Finland from OP Public Services Real Estate Fund. WAULT 10 years.

Construction will be divided into three parts; the first part includes 35,000 sqm of warehouse and technical premises. Posti's subsidiary Transval will occupy the premises. The plot area is 18.7 ha.
Kesko acquires a logistics plot in Nurmijärvi to develop a new logistics centre. Total building right is 314,265 sqm. Plot area is 714,000 sqm.
Ethos Capital acquires three logistics properties from DEAS Property Fund Finland I. Two of the properties are located in Pori and one in Kangasala. Price is not disclosed.
Hartela acquires two plots in Olari, Espoo from the city of Espoo. Total building rights are 7,146 sqm and 1,513 sqm.

WAULT 0.8 years.

Aedfica divests a portfolio of 10 day care properties. Average capacity for the portfolio is approx. 875 children. The portfolio was built by Hoivatilat in 2012-2020 and is operated by Touhula, Pilke, Norlandia and Murunen.
Y-Säätiö acquired 73 apartments from three healthcare properties in Helsinki, Turku and Hämeenlinna. The anchor tenant is Validia Oy.
Six light industrial and warehouse properties in Helsinki and Vantaa. Sale and leaseback arrangement with MEKO. Triple-net leases with NOI €2.5m. WAULT 10 years.

KKR makes their first investment in the Nordics through their European Core Plus Real Estate-strategy. 30 residential properties, 1,200 apartments in total, of which 2/3 are in Helsinki, Turku and Tampere. Price is not disclosed but the deal is the largest real estate transaction in Finland 2023
Two residential properties to be built in Espoo and Tampere. Construction will begin in Summer 2023 with estimated completion in the begin of 2025.
Aktiivitilat acquired a warehouse property in Juvanmalmi, Espoo. The property has been constructed in 1970 and is fully let to Medifon.

Evli acquired a shopping center Ristikko located in Konala, Helsinki from Hartela and Ilmarinen. The property has been constructed in 2009 and an extension completed in 2015. 95% occupancy, WAULT 4.2 years, NOI €1.7m.
Sagax acquired four fully let light industrial properties in Oulu. Properties are constructed in 2018-2023. WAULT 8 years. NOI €1.29m.
Aktiivitilat will acquire an industrial property in Ylästö, Vantaa. The property has been constructed in 1997 and it has approx. 8,000 sqm of unused building right.
Retail warehouse property currently under construction in Varisto, Vantaa. Main tenants will be Puuilo and Saka.
Two residential / apartment hotel properties in Helsinki, both let to Forenom. Initial yield 10%.

eQ fund investing in a public property in Niittykumpu, Espoo. The property is currently being converted from office to public use. Approx. 1/3 of GLA will be let to City of Espoo with a 15-year lease agreement.
Aedifica acquires two new healthcare properties in Helsinki and Salo. Gross yield 6%.

column4: Swiss Life Asset Managers Transactions AS
column11: A hospital property in Lahti. Fully let to the city of Lahti with a WAULT of 13 years. Net initial yield 5.8%.
CapMan divesting an office property (YoC 1979) in Hämeenlinna. CapMan had acquired the property in February 2007.

Aberdeen fund divesting a warehouse property (YoC 2005) close to Helsinki-Vantaa airport to an undisclosed investor. The property is fully let to PostNord with a WAULT of 4.1 years. Initial yield 5.0%.

column11: DEAS fund divesting an industrial and office property in Jyväskylä. The property is currently let to Cramo, but they will relocate their business to new premises. The buyers are owner-occupiers.
Three modern residential properties including 226 residential units located in Helsinki metropolitan area.
Two industrial properties (concrete factories) located in Oulu, let to Parma which is a part of Consolis group. WAULT almost 10 years.
Innovestor acquires a new construction retail / big box property in Kaarina. Anchor tenant will be Byggmax.

Historical mixed-use property located in Hernesaari, close to Helsinki CBD. The property has been built in 1946 as a factory of Ford.

Corum divesting two retail big box properties anchored by Tokmanni.

eQ selling five care homes in Helsinki region (Kirkkonummi, Järvenpää, Vihti), in Ylöjärvi and in Joensuu.
Sale and leaseback arrangement between special investment fund Evli Vuokratuotto and owner-occupier.

Norwegian Kinland acquires 28 social infrastructure properties (18 pre-school and 10 care properties) from eQ Community Properties in two transactions. Majority of the properties are located in the largest cities of Finland.

13 public use and healthcare properties in Jyväskylä, all let to the City of Jyväskylä with long WALT (17.4 years). Yield was 5.7%, original bid in June 2022 was €85.56m (5.6%). A land area sold as a part of a larger development project in Turku city center.

A sale and leaseback arrangement between UKK, a healthcare sector owner-occupier and a local investor.

Sagax has sold three office properties to Ovaro. Two of the properties are located in Jyväskylä city center and one in the university campus. The current occupancy rate of the properties is some 70% and yield 7.4%.

column11: An owner-occupier selling two light industrial properties in strong locations in Juvanmalmi, Espoo and in Pirkkala, Tampere region.

Office property Ilmalan Aura is currently under construction and will be completed in 2024. 70% of the premises have been let to in total three tenants.

Office property (YoC 2008) located in Pasila.
Two car retail and repair properties under construction.

An office property with excellent location, visible in the immediate vicinity of the upcoming Jokeri Light Rail line stop close to the Haaga traffic circle.
